Package com.microfocus.adm.pulse.pluginapi.chain.dto

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    PulseChainContext
    A chain run executes its steps sequentially one by one, where each plugin is invoked with an instance of this interface to describe the current state of the chain run.
    PulseChange
    Describes one change that makes up the changeset.
    PulseChangeset
    Describes the changes that make up the changeset within the repository that is to be analysed by the expert.
    PulseEmail
    Represents email message that will be sent to Pulse users.
    PulseFinding
    Represents something that has been discovered about either the whole file or a particular line in the file.
    PulseMeasurement
    Represents a measurement made by an expert of a metric.
    PulseMetric
    This interface represents a metric definition within the Pulse framework and is required in order for an expert to make a metric measurement.
    PulseRequest
    Where a changeset is associated with a request, this interface provides a means of requesting additional information about the request.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    PulseChainStepPluginCategory
    Provides a known set of categories that experts can implement.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    LogLevel  
    PulseChange.ChangeType
    Type of change a PulseChange represents:
    PulseFindingSeverity
    The severity of the PulseFinding:
    PulseFindingType
    The type of the PulseFinding:
    PulseMetricCoreRealm
    All metrics belong to a realm that helps to group the metrics together into similar blocks of measurement types.
    PulseMetricDirection
    Indicates whether an increasing value is better or worse.
    PulseMetricStorage
    Describes whether a measurement for a metric is PulseMetricStorage.TRANSIENT and shouldn't be recorded in the datatbase or PulseMetricStorage.DATABASE where it should be recorded in the database.
    PulseMetricType
    The metric type can be one of: PulseMetricType.INTEGER PulseMetricType.STRING PulseMetricType.DOUBLE PulseMetricType.BOOLEAN PulseMetricType.DURATION PulseMetricType.SCALE PulseMetricType.SEVERITY
    PulseState
    Indicates the state of the chain plugin to the Pulse framework.
